---
// TeamBlock.astro, About page Ryan section

---

<section
  class="py-24 md:py-32 bg-black"
  aria-labelledby="team-heading"
>
  <div class="container mx-auto px-6 md:px-12 max-w-7xl">
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 md:gap-20 items-center">

      <!-- Photo: left column -->
      <div
        class="opacity-0 relative"
        data-reveal="slide-left"
      >
        <div class="relative w-full aspect-[3/4] max-w-md mx-auto md:mx-0 rounded-xl overflow-hidden">

          <!-- Ryan's photo -->
          <img
            src="/images/ryan.jpg"
            alt="Ryan van der Niet filming at a festival"
            class="w-full h-full object-cover"
          />

          <!-- Gradient overlay -->
          <div
            class="absolute inset-0 pointer-events-none"
            style="background: linear-gradient(to bottom, transparent 50%, rgba(0,0,0,0.6) 100%);"
          ></div>

          <!-- Corner accents -->
          <div class="absolute top-5 left-5 w-8 h-8 border-t-2 border-l-2 border-white/10"></div>
          <div class="absolute bottom-5 right-5 w-8 h-8 border-b-2 border-r-2 border-white/10"></div>

        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Text: right column -->
      <div
        class="opacity-0 flex flex-col gap-8"
        data-reveal="slide-right"
      >

        <!-- Label -->
        <span class="text-sm uppercase tracking-[0.25em] text-white/40 font-medium">
          The Founder
        </span>

        <!-- Name + title -->
        <div class="flex flex-col gap-2">
          <h2
            id="team-heading"
            class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black italic leading-tight tracking-tight text-white"
          >
            Ryan van der Niet
          </h2>
          <p class="text-sm uppercase tracking-wider text-white/40 font-medium">
            Creative Director
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Story paragraphs -->
        <div class="flex flex-col gap-5">

          <p class="text-base text-white/60 leading-relaxed">
            Ryan started as a harder styles influencer with a deep passion for music. What began as
            sharing the scene online quickly grew into managing social media accounts for artists,
            and eventually picking up a camera to capture the energy himself.
          </p>

          <p class="text-base text-white/60 leading-relaxed">
            Over the years, he worked alongside major artists and festivals across the Netherlands,
            building a reputation for content that felt real, high-energy, and built for the scroll.
          </p>

          <p class="text-base text-white/60 leading-relaxed">
            That's what led him to build Capture &amp; Connect, an agency that combines content creation
            and social media management into one system. From filming events and editing cinematic visuals
            to posting and growing your audience.
          </p>

          <p class="text-base text-white/60 leading-relaxed">
            Today, Ryan leads a team of creatives focused on one thing: turning content into results.
            Every project is personal, every number is real.
          </p>

        </div>

        <!-- Social proof / CTA -->
        <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-start sm:items-center gap-6 pt-2">
          <a
            href="mailto:info@captureandconnect.nl"
            class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-6 py-3 bg-white text-black font-semibold text-sm tracking-widest uppercase transition-all duration-300 hover:bg-white/90 hover:scale-[1.02] rounded-none"
          >
            Work With Ryan
          </a>

          <!-- Divider -->
          <div class="hidden sm:block w-px h-6 bg-white/10" aria-hidden="true"></div>

          <!-- Quick credential -->
          <p class="text-xs text-white/30 leading-relaxed">
            Based in the Netherlands<br />
            Serving artists &amp; brands worldwide
          </p>
        </div>

      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>
